All Implemented Interfaces:
BranchRates, TreeTrait<java.lang.Double>, TreeTraitProvider, BranchRateModel, Loggable, Likelihood, Model, ModelListener, StatisticList, VariableListener, MPISerializable, Identifiable, java.io.Serializable
public class ACLikelihood
extends RateEvolutionLikelihood

Calculates the likelihood of a set of rate changes in a tree, assuming a (log)normal or inverse gaussian distributed change in rate at each node, with a mean of the previous (log) rate and a variance proportional to branch length. cf Yang and Rannala 2006

Author:
Michael Defoin Platel, Wai Lok Sibon Li
